---
import ArtfulyLayout from '../../layouts/ArtfulyLayout.astro';
---

<ArtfulyLayout
  title="Ticklists — Repeating Lists & Daily Routines · Artfuly Tools"
  description="A free productivity app for shopping lists and daily routines that never need rewriting. Items can repeat daily/some days or weekly, sort into sections automatically, and sync live with your household."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="articles-section-top">
    <div class="a-container w-container">
      <div class="a-des-insight-title" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6); margin-bottom:12px; grid-area:1/1/2/5; text-align:left">FREE TOOL</div>
      <h1 class="h1-small-white" style="grid-area:2/1/3/5; padding-left:0">Ticklists</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HERO IMAGE -->
  <div class="section-47">
    <address style="background-image:url('/images/tools/ticklists-tool-hero.png'); background-size:cover; background-position:center top" class="div-with-collection-image">
      <div class="gradient-div"></div>
    </address>
  </div>

  <!-- BODY -->
  <div style="padding: 3rem 0 2rem;">
    <div class="a-4col-grid-container w-container">

      <div style="grid-area:1/1/2/5">
        <h2 class="h2-small-blue-blog">Stop rewriting the same lists, over and over.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="w-richtext" style="grid-area:2/1/3/5; align-self:start">

        <p>Most list apps treat every item as a one-time task — tick it, it disappears, you retype it next week. Ticklists works differently: items stay on your list and repeat on the days you choose — daily, specific weekdays, or every week. Tick when done, untick when needed again. The list is always ready, and you never type the same thing twice.</p>

        <h3>Built for repetitive routines</h3>
        <p>Whether it's a weekly food shop, a morning routine, a property maintenance schedule, or a daily work checklist — Ticklists is built around the reality that most of what we do, we do again. The app keeps your lists intact and organised, so your focus stays on getting things done rather than managing the list itself.</p>

        <h3>Sections that sort themselves</h3>
        <p>Assign each item to a section once — store departments for shopping lists, time blocks for routines — and the list reorders itself automatically every time. No more wandering back and forth across the supermarket. No more forgetting which step comes next.</p>

        <h3>Shared household lists</h3>
        <p>Share a list with your household and see each other's ticks in real time. No more "did you get the milk?" texts. Works across Android, Mac, tablet, and any browser — no App Store required.</p>

        <h3>Tags for flexible filtering</h3>
        <p>Add custom tags to items — Keto, Campervan, Parents visit — and filter your list to show only what's relevant right now. One master list, many contexts.</p>

        <h3>Who it's for</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Households managing shared weekly shopping</li>
          <li>Anyone with ADHD who needs structure without friction</li>
          <li>Property owners with recurring maintenance tasks</li>
          <li>Shift workers and small businesses with repeating operational checklists</li>
          <li>Anyone exhausted by rewriting the same things every week</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Ticklists is a Progressive Web App — install it from your browser on any device, no app store needed. Free to use, with a Pro plan for power users.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="article-cta-section">
    <a href="https://ticklists.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="tutor-btn tutor-btn--coral article-cta-btn">
      Try Ticklists free →
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- EMAIL SIGNUP -->
  <section class="section_cta8" id="email-signup">
    <div class="padding-global-3">
      <div class="container-large">
        <div class="padding-section-large-3">
          <div class="cta8_component">
            <div class="cta8_content">
              <div class="max-width-large">
                <div class="margin-bottom margin-xsmall">
                  <div class="margin-bottom margin-xsmall">
                    <div class="a-des-insight-title">WEEKLY EMAIL (FREE)</div>
                  </div>
                  <h2 class="white h2insights">The Design Edge</h2>
                </div>
                <p class="white right">Keep your design skills up to date with videos,<br />AI workflows, tutorials, ways to earn $$$ and free resources</p>
                <p class="small-white-body">Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="html-embed-7 w-embed w-script">
              <script async data-uid="eb98b5a075" src="https://artfuly.ck.page/eb98b5a075/index.js"></script>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</ArtfulyLayout>
